bilingual.source: I've decided to go on a diet!
She started a diet to lose weight.
He measured his waistline before starting the diet.
bilingual.target: 他在开始节食前量了他的腰围。

bilingual.source: He lost a significant amount of peso after his diet.
bilingual.target: 他在节食后减掉了大量的重量。

bilingual.source: She is always indulging in sweets despite her diet.
bilingual.target: 尽管在节食，她总是沉溺于甜食。

bilingual.source: She refrained from eating sweets during her diet.
bilingual.target: 她在节食期间克制住自己不吃甜食。

bilingual.source: He found that diet was very helpful for his health.
bilingual.target: 他发现节食对他的健康有很大帮助。

bilingual.source: Diet does not mean you can't eat delicious food.
bilingual.target: 节食并不意味着你不能吃美味的食物。

bilingual.source: Her diet plan includes eating more fruits and vegetables.
bilingual.target: 她的节食计划包括多吃水果和蔬菜。

bilingual.source: He was scoffing at the idea of going on a diet.

list.abstract: 《Diet》是由歌手Au Pairs演唱的一首英文歌曲，收录于2008年8月29日发行的专辑《Stepping Out Of Line - The Anthology》中。

yingyinNormal.en: Is it diet? That's what you ordered. Thank you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是无糖的吗？这就是你点的，谢谢。

yingyinNormal.en: These diet beverages still pose serious health risks.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但这些无糖饮料依旧威胁着你的健康。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《可口可乐史上最诚实的广告》

yingyinNormal.en: A balanced diet means vegetables, kiddo. Get used to it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 平衡膳食的意思就是要有蔬菜，孩子。好好习惯吧。

yingyinNormal.en: And would you make it diet? There's a can in the fridge.
yingyinNormal.zh: 能调制成无糖的吗？冰箱里有罐装的。

yingyinNormal.en: Sheldon, what are you going to have? I'll have a diet coke.
yingyinNormal.zh: 谢尔顿，你要什么？我要一杯无糖可乐。

yingyinNormal.en: Juice or soda? Diet something, if you got it. Who are they?
yingyinNormal.zh: 喝果汁还是汽水？低热量的就行，如果你有的话照片上是谁？

yingyinNormal.en: What kind of a diet doesn't allow tequila? All of them, actually.
yingyinNormal.zh: 什么样饭局连龙舌兰都不能喝？其实，所有的饭局都不能喝。

yingyinNormal.en: Yes. Okay.Tortilla chips, yogurt. Diet soda. Yes. Yes. Yes. Orange juice.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有苹果，玉米片，酸奶，健怡汽水。对。柳橙汁。

yingyinNormal.en: If there's a single food that symbolizes the American diet for me, it's beef.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果有一种食物能作为美国食品的标志，非牛肉莫属。

yingyinNormal.en: Why are you yelling? Whoa, that Diet Coke I think just straight to my head. Woo.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你干嘛这么大声？这杯健怡可乐让我好兴奋。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey Joe. Yeah, can I get a 3-piece, some cole slaw, some beans, and a Coke, Diet Coke.
yingyinNormal.zh: 乔伊！我想要三块鸡，沙拉，豆子，还有可乐，健怡可乐。

yingyinNormal.en: Here you go honey. One Diet Coke with ice. Oh, thank you. I'm so happy that you're here.
yingyinNormal.zh: 来了，一杯加冰的健怡可乐。谢谢，真高兴有你在。

yingyinNormal.en: In order to live long enough to fuse my consciousness with cybernetics, I need to change my diet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 为了把我的寿命延长到能把意识转移到人造大脑上，我要改变饮食。

yingyinNormal.en: I mean, if a slimy reptile found them appetizing, there was certainly no place for them in my diet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 黏糊糊软趴趴的动物喜欢的食物，我想想都觉得恶心。

yingyinNormal.en: Tadashi was in excellent health. With a proper diet and exercise, he should have lived a long life.
yingyinNormal.zh: 阿正身体十分健康，饮食健康，坚持锻炼，他应该会长寿。

yingyinNormal.en: Here you go honey. Thank you. Diet Coke. Op, ice. I need ice. Okay. Thank you. I'll be right back. Okay.
yingyinNormal.zh: 拿来了，亲爱的。谢谢你，健怡可乐冰块，我要冰块。好。谢谢你。我马上回来。好。

yingyinNormal.en: Hi. My friend ordered an onion, not an olive, and I ordered a rum and Diet Coke, which I don't think this is.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我朋友点的是洋葱，不是橄榄，我点的是甜酒和健怡可乐，这杯不是。

yingyinNormal.en: Honey, we don't have any bears here. Well, okay. Would you get me a Diet Coke? Okay. I'll be right back. Okay.
yingyinNormal.zh: 亲爱的，这里没有熊。好吧，帮我倒杯健怡可乐好吗？好，我马上回来。好。

yingyinNormal.en: But scientists have estimated that sauropods ate about 1,500kg of hay every day. In other words, about 20 times that daily diet. Or 50 bales of hay.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但科学家经过估算后发现蜥脚龙每天大约能吃掉1.5吨草料。换句话说 相当于大象的二十倍，或者是50捆干草。

sense_info_list.en: the food and drink usually eaten or drunk by a person or group

examination_example.sentence: But switching to a mainly plant-based <highlight>diet</highlight> wouldn't help.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是转向以植物为主的饮食不会有帮助。

examination_example.sentence: The two highly recommended lifestyle approaches are maintaining or increasing your level of aerobic exercise and following a Mediterranean-style <highlight>diet</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 两种非常推荐的生活方式是保持或提高你的有氧运动水平以及遵循地中海式饮食。

examination_example.sentence: Stop laughing: it's not just cost effective but helps you balance your <highlight>diet</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 别笑了：这不仅划算，还能帮你平衡饮食。

examination_example.sentence: Websites about <highlight>dieting</highlight> would thrive.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 关于节食的网站会蓬勃发展。

examination_example.sentence: They hint that people should look to intangible qualities like character and intellect rather than <highlight>dieting</highlight> their way to size zero or wasp-waist physiques.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们暗示，人们应该关注像性格和智力这样无形的品质，而不是通过节食减肥达到零号或蜂腰身材。

examination_example.sentence: The parliament also agreed to ban websites that "incite excessive thinness" by promoting extreme <highlight>dieting</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 议会还同意取缔通过宣传极端节食来“煽动过度瘦身”的网站。

examination_example.sentence: It would force poor people to change their <highlight>diet</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这将迫使穷人改变他们的饮食。

examination_example.sentence: The low-carbohydrate food movement gave birth to such <highlight>diets</highlight> as the Atkins, Paleo and Keto.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 低碳水化合物食品运动催生了诸如阿特金斯(Atkins)，克洛(Paleo)和基多(Keto)等饮食法。

examination_example.sentence: They enjoy a higher life expectancy, presumably reflecting advantages with respect to health care, <highlight>diet</highlight>, lifestyle, and the like.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们的预期寿命较高，反映其在保健、饮食、生活方式等方面的优势。

examination_example.sentence: It's a narrative often drowned out by the shame that marketers rely on to peddle us their <highlight>diet</highlight> pills and breathable yoga pants.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但这种说法经常被一种耻辱所淹没，那就是商人们依赖于向我们兜售他们的减肥药和透气瑜伽裤。

examination_example.sentence: The researchers argued that breakfast helps reduce daily calorie intake and improve the quality of our <highlight>diet</highlight> — since breakfast foods are often higher in fibre and nutrients.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 研究人员认为，早餐有助于减少每日卡路里的摄入量，改善我们的饮食质量，因为早餐吃的东西往往含有更高的纤维含量和营养成分。

examination_example.sentence: The Eskimos of Greenland have developed certain genetic adaptations that help them digest and utilize this fat-rich <highlight>diet</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 爱斯基摩人已经进化出有助于其消化并利用这种高脂饮食的某些遗传适应性。

examination_example.sentence: In general, many lifestyle medicine physicians recommend a plant-based <highlight>diet</highlight> — particularly for people with diabetes or other inflammatory conditions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一般来说，许多生活方式医学医生建议以植物为基础的饮食，特别是对于糖尿病或其他炎症患者。

examination_example.sentence: The salt, sugar, fat and processed foods in the American <highlight>diet</highlight> contribute to the nation's high rates of obesity, diabetes and heart disease.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 美国人饮食中的盐、糖、脂肪和加工食品导致了美国肥胖症、糖尿病和心脏病的高发率。

examination_example.sentence: Research findings increasingly show the power of food to treat or reverse diseases, but that does not mean that <highlight>diet</highlight> alone is always the solution, or that every illness can benefit substantially from dietary changes.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 研究结果越来越多地显示出食物治疗或逆转疾病的力量，但这并不意味着仅靠饮食就一定能解决问题，也不意味着每一种疾病都能从饮食改变中大大改善。

examination_example.sentence: Exercise is more important to good health than <highlight>diet</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 比起节食，锻炼对健康更重要。

examination_example.sentence: Americans spend billions of dollars each year trying to change their weight with <highlight>diets</highlight>, gym memberships and plastic surgery.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 美国人每年花费数十亿美元试图通过节食、健身和整形手术来改变体重。

examination_example.sentence: Her mother told her to <highlight>diet</highlight> when she was only 8 years old.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她妈妈在她只有8岁的时候就告诉她要节食。

examination_example.sentence: Mrs. White, I'm afraid we have to put you on a strict <highlight>diet</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 怀特太太，恐怕我们必须严格控制你的饮食。

examination_example.sentence: You will stick to your <highlight>diet</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你将坚持你的饮食。

examination_example.sentence: Here are some ways to turn your home into part of your <highlight>diet</highlight> plan.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这里有一些方法可以把你的家变成你饮食计划的一部分。

examination_example.sentence: Rice is a big part of the Chinese <highlight>diet</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大米是中国人饮食的重要组成部分。

examination_example.sentence: Vegetarians eat a low-fat <highlight>diet</highlight> to stay fit and healthy.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 素食主义者吃低脂饮食以保持健康。

examination_example.sentence: First, you have to pay more attention to your <highlight>diet</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 首先，你必须更加注意你的饮食。

examination_example.sentence: Pet pigs must be kept on a <highlight>diet</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 宠物猪必须保持节食。

examination_example.sentence: More than half the teenage girls in the USA, think they should be on a <highlight>diet</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 美国超过一半的女孩认为她们应该节食。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Diet</highlight> drinks are not quite as healthy as you think.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 低热量饮料并不像你想象的那么健康。
